metadata.name: Next in line
metadata.description:
In this project Andrei Chino compares the development of AI technologies with the emergence of some new religion for humanity of the future and is aimed at finding new "holy" images for future generations "improved" by technologies (including AI). 
To do this, the author uses his so-called "Artificial AI" technology: manual processing of large arrays of random images generated by AI and the subsequent "human" search and identification of new images from digital chaos.

MP4 video, 1080 x 1920 px
